## 2. `collector_summary.txt` -- full schema

The file is divided into sections delimited by `## ` headers. Every section
is optional except `# AMAMA collector summary` (the file header) and
`## Processes`.

### 2.1 File header (always)

```
# AMAMA collector summary
schema: 1
image: memory.raw  sha256: ab12...4b3  profile: Win10x64_19041  size: 4.0 GB
acquired: 2025-08-08T14:35:12Z   collector_ms: 3421
```

- `schema` is the format version (bump on breaking changes).
- `image` line is one space-separated row of key=value-ish pairs. Use
  `...` to elide long hashes (full hash in `collector_deep.json`).
- `acquired` is from the memory image (vol3 windows.info plugin) when
  available, else the file mtime.
- `collector_ms` is wall-clock duration of the collector run.

### 2.2 `## Process tree` (always)

ASCII tree of every process. Indent = 2 spaces per depth.

```
## Process tree
System (4)
  smss.exe (412)
  ...
explorer.exe (6088) user=alice
  WINWORD.EXE (6240) signed
    rundll32.exe (6612) flags=spawned_by_office,loads_unsigned_dll
      svchost.exe (4920) user=SYSTEM flags=wrong_path,unsigned,lsass_handle,external_conn
[orphans: 9999, 12108]
```

Rules:
- Format per line: `<name> (<pid>) [optional space-separated key=val or flag tokens]`
- Only short tags inline: `signed`, `user=alice`, `flags=a,b,c`. Anything
  longer goes in the per-process detail below.
- Trailing `[orphans: ...]` line lists PIDs whose parent is missing from
  the dump. Always present (empty list is `[orphans: none]`).

### 2.3 `## Processes` (always, flagged only)

**Only flagged processes appear here.** Unflagged ones are in the tree
above and in `collector_deep.json`, but Agent 1 doesn't need to see them.
This is the biggest token-saver in the file.

```
## Processes (5 flagged)
* PID 4920 svchost.exe
  path: C:\Users\Public\svchost.exe
  ppid: 6612 (rundll32.exe)
  user: SYSTEM
  started: 2025-08-08T14:32:01Z
  metrics: dlls=23 handles=187 threads=8
  net: 1 conn, external 185.220.101.5:443
  flags: wrong_path, unsigned, parent_is_lolbin, lsass_handle, external_conn
  linked_persistence: p1
  cmdline_preview: C:\Users\Public\svchost.exe -k netsvcs

* PID 6612 rundll32.exe
  path: C:\Windows\System32\rundll32.exe
  ppid: 6240 (WINWORD.EXE)
  user: alice
  started: 2025-08-08T14:32:00Z
  metrics: dlls=18 handles=92 threads=4
  flags: spawned_by_office, loads_unsigned_dll
  cmdline_preview: rundll32.exe "C:\ProgramData\winhelp.dll",Start
```

Rules:
- `* PID <n> <name>` starts each entry. The asterisk gives the LLM a
  reliable bullet to anchor on.
- Field order is fixed (path, ppid, user, started, metrics, net, flags,
  linked_persistence, cmdline_preview). Missing fields are simply omitted.
- `metrics` is a single line of `key=value` pairs, no quotes.
- `net` is a one-line summary: `<n> conn[s], <external|internal> <ip:port>[, ...]`.
  Omit if zero connections.
- `flags` is comma-separated lowercase tokens (see flag taxonomy below).
- `linked_persistence` references IDs from the persistence section.
- `cmdline_preview` is truncated to ~120 chars; full cmdline in deep index.

### 2.4 `## Persistence` (when non-empty)

```
## Persistence (2)
[p1] service "WinHelpSvc" start=Auto image=C:\ProgramData\winhelp.exe
     linked_pid=4920  flags=unsigned, non_system_path
[p2] task "\Microsoft\Windows\Maintenance\WinUpd" cmd=C:\ProgramData\winhelp.exe -u
     linked_pid=null  flags=masquerades_as_update, shared_binary_with:p1
[p3] registry_run key=HKLM\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run val=updater data=...
     linked_pid=null  flags=hidden_value
```

Rules:
- `[<id>] <type> "<name>" <key>=<value> ...` first line, continuation
  indented 5 spaces.
- IDs are `p1`, `p2`, ... and are referenced from `## Processes` via
  `linked_persistence`.
- `linked_pid` is `null` when the persisted binary isn't currently
  running. `shared_binary_with:pN` flag highlights deduplication.

### 2.5 `## Time clusters` (when any)

Pre-computed bursts of new processes. Saves Agent 1 from doing time math.

```
## Time clusters (1)
[t1] 14:32:00..14:33:30Z user=alice  new=[6612, 4920]  flags=burst_after_office_open
```

A "cluster" is any window with >= 2 unsigned-or-flagged process starts
within 60 seconds for the same user.

### 2.6 `## Network` (when any external conns)

```
## Network (3 external)
185.220.101.5:443  pid=4920 svchost.exe  rfc1918=no  flags=external
51.83.200.12:8443  pid=4920 svchost.exe  rfc1918=no  flags=external,unusual_port
```

Internal connections are not listed here (they're in the per-process
`net:` line + deep index).

### 2.7 `## Counts` (always, last)

A single-line audit so Agent 1 can sanity-check what it's seeing.

```
## Counts
processes=187 (5 flagged), services=198 (1 flagged), tasks=23 (1 flagged),
unsigned_binaries=6, external_conns=3, orphans=2
```

