## 4. Volatility 3 plugin mapping

Where each piece of data comes from. The collector calls these in order
and pipes their iterators into the build step.

| vol3 plugin                                  | feeds into                                          |
|----------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| `windows.info.Info`                          | image_info (profile, acquired)                      |
| `windows.pslist.PsList`                      | by_pid.{pid,ppid,name,user,started,exited,threads}  |
| `windows.pstree.PsTree`                      | process_tree (edges + orphans)                      |
| `windows.cmdline.CmdLine`                    | by_pid.cmdline + summary.cmdline_preview            |
| `windows.privileges.Privs`                   | by_pid.privileges                                   |
| `windows.handles.Handles`                    | by_pid.handles                                      |
| `windows.dlllist.DllList`                    | by_pid.dlllist                                      |
| `windows.envars.Envars`                      | by_pid.envars                                       |
| `windows.netscan.NetScan`                    | by_pid.network + summary `## Network`               |
| `windows.netstat.NetStat` (fallback)         | same as above for newer Win10 builds                |
| `windows.malfind.Malfind`                    | by_pid.malfind + injection flags                    |
| `windows.svcscan.SvcScan`                    | persistence (type=service)                          |
| `windows.registry.printkey.PrintKey`         | by_path.registry_printkey + persistence (Run keys)  |
| `windows.filescan.FileScan`                  | by_path.filescan                                    |
| `windows.amcache.Amcache` (optional)         | execution evidence; populates flags `executed_in_amcache` |
| `windows.scheduled_tasks.ScheduledTasks`     | persistence (type=task)                             |

The collector should be **defensive**: if a plugin fails (common with
mismatched symbols), it logs to `collector.log` and continues, marking the
missing data in `image.degraded_plugins: ["malfind", ...]` inside the
deep file.

